    "Metadata": {
        "Id": "08ff1cd1-d648-48c0-b073-60e375b0a7c6",
        "Type": "usercreated",
        "Title": "Ugly Duckling Fight Back !",
        "Location": "LOCATION_ELEGANT_LLAMA",
        "PublicId": "131101398105",
        "ScenePath": "assembly:/_pro/scenes/missions/elegant/scene_llama.entity",
        "TileImage": "$($repository 6ca02d70-ce2d-467f-a908-f6b93b685f38).Image",
        "Description": "I&#39;m sure we all familiar with Ugly Duckling Story. If you forgot or didn&#39;t know, here a bit refresher. \r\rAfter a mother duck's eggs hatch, one of the ducklings is perceived by the other animals as an ugly little creature and suffers much verbal and physical abuse. \r\rHe wanders from the barnyard and lives with wild ducks and geese until hunters slaughter the flocks. He finds a home with an old woman, but her cat and hen tease and taunt him mercilessly, and once again he sets off alone.\r\rThe duckling sees a flock of migrating wild swans. He is delighted and excited but cannot join them, for he is too young, ugly, and unable to fly. When winter arrives, a farmer finds and carries the freezing duckling home, but he is frightened by the farmer's noisy children and flees the house. The duckling spends a miserable winter alone outdoors, mostly hiding in a cave on the lake that partly freezes over.\r\rThe duckling, now having fully grown and matured, cannot endure a life of solitude and hardship anymore. He decides to throw himself at a flock of swans, feeling that it is better to be killed by such beautiful birds than to live a life of ugliness. He is shocked when the swans welcome and accept him, only to realize by looking at his reflection in the water that he had been not a duckling but a swan all this time. The flock takes to the air, and he spreads his wings to take flight with the rest of his new family.\r\r\r\r\r\rNot 47 of course, he fight back! He doesn&#39;t wait until he become a swan to get revenge. He kill his whole family except Mommy Tamara Vidal.",
        "GameVersion": "8.10.0.49",
        "IsPublished": true,
        "Entitlements": [
            "LOCATION_ELEGANT"
        ],
